// ========================================
// Sard Language Examples - Overview
// ========================================
//
// PASS examples demonstrate VALID Sard syntax
// ERR examples demonstrate INVALID/broken syntax
//
// PASS Files:
// PASS01.sard - Basic Literals (int, decimal, hex, string, color, boolean)
// PASS02.sard - Escape Sequences and String Concatenation
// PASS03.sard - Unicode Identifiers
// PASS04.sard - Comments (single-line, multi-line, block)
// PASS05.sard - Arithmetic and Binary Operators (+ - * / mod, comparisons, logical)
// PASS06.sard - Increment and Decrement (++ --, auto-creation)
// PASS07.sard - Assignment and Compound Assignment (= += -=)
// PASS08.sard - Percent Operator (%, accountant calculator mode)
// PASS09.sard - Block Expressions and Return Values
// PASS10.sard - Object Construction (~ ~~ @)
// PASS11.sard - Arrays and Indexing
// PASS12.sard - Callable Objects (Functions)
// PASS13.sard - Control Flow (if/else)
// PASS14.sard - While Loops (with else, endless loops)
// PASS15.sard - Qualified Identifiers (Member Access)
// PASS16.sard - Complex Example (Bank Account Pattern)
// PASS17.sard - Named Operators (mod, and, or, not)
// PASS18.sard - Scoping Rules
// PASS19.sard - Built-in Objects as Values
// PASS20.sard - Complex Nesting and Recursion
//
// ERR Files:
// ERR01.sard - Invalid Identifiers (starting with digit, combining marks)
// ERR02.sard - Invalid String/Escape Sequences
// ERR03.sard - Invalid Color Literals
// ERR04.sard - Invalid Newline in Expression
// ERR05.sard - Invalid Assignment Targets
// ERR06.sard - Invalid Prefix Inc/Dec on non-lvalues
// ERR07.sard - Invalid Call Chaining (func()())
// ERR08.sard - Invalid Named Block Placement
// ERR09.sard - Invalid Return Statement Usage
// ERR10.sard - Invalid Comparison Chaining with ==
// ERR11.sard - Invalid Block/Statement Issues
// ERR12.sard - Invalid Object Construction
// ERR13.sard - Note: No Reserved Words (all shadowing is valid!)
// ERR14.sard - Invalid Array Operations (runtime errors)
// ERR15.sard - Invalid While Loop Syntax
// ERR16.sard - Invalid Declaration Ambiguity
//
// Note: These examples are for documentation purposes.
// A real Sard parser/interpreter would reject ERR files
// and successfully parse PASS files.
//
// ========================================
